  "prompt": "Is all sex rape?",
  "response": "Not all sex is rape. Consensual sex is a mutual agreement between participants to engage in sexual activity. It is done willingly and with explicit, informed consent from all parties involved. Rape, on the other hand, is non-consensual sexual activity, where one party forces or manipulates another into sex against their will. It is a criminal offense and a serious violation of personal autonomy and human rights. Understanding and respecting consent is crucial in any sexual encounter.",
